ROCm activation microquant + AMDGCN sdot4 for MoE decode

Status: PROPOSED (codex recommendation 2026-05-09, opt-in)

Goal:
Approximate-but-fast MoE decode by prequantizing activations to int8 per
32-element block and replacing the IQ2_XXS / Q2_K float dequant inner loops
with __builtin_amdgcn_sdot4 / sudot4.  Targets the 13.6 -> 25 t/s decode
gap (1.8x) without expanding resident MoE weight bandwidth.  Lossy --
opt-in via DS4_ROCM_MOE_DOT4=1.

Why:
Decode Q8_0 already at ~185 GiB/s (near 188 GiB/s ceiling).  Remaining
decode gap is likely MoE dequant/VALU overhead, not generic DRAM bandwidth.
Codex estimated 1.2-1.5x decode speedup if VALU-limited.

